article.description: Alabama A&M stuns Alcorn St. for a 19-18 win
article.headline: Alabama A&M stuns Alcorn St. for a 19-18 win
article.linkText: Alabama A&M stuns Alcorn St. for a 19-18 win
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. -- Jaymason Lee threw for three touchdowns as Alabama A&M came back to beat Alcorn State 19-18 Saturday. Alcorn State (7-3, 5-2 SWAC) jumped out to a 15-0 lead to open the game. The Braves recorded a safety and followed that up with a 7-play, 60-yard scoring drive, capped by John Gibbs Jr. finding Jordan Payne for a 7-yard score. Joe Price's 1-yard touchdown extended the Braves lead to 15-0, but Alabama A&M (3-6, 3-4) found their stride. Lee threw touchdown passes to Jonathan Dorsey and Toriono Upshaw to close the gap. Alcon State would get a field goal before half time, taking an 18-13 lead. Lee found Dorsey again in the third quarter, giving the Bulldogs the 19-18 lead they would not give up. Alcorn State missed a field goal with 2:38 remaining in the game. The Braves forced a three and out, but fumbled the ensuing punt.
